Sentencas: The direct utilization of methanol (MeOH) and ethanol (EtOH) was investigated on Cu-Co(Ru)/Zr0.35Ce0.65O2 anodes for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFC) prepared by impregnation.
Titulo: Direct utilization of methanol and ethanol in solid oxide fuel cells using Cu-Co(Ru)/Zr0.35Ce0.65O2-δ anodes

Sentencas: Cells had similar performance and stability in H-2 and MeOH, while in EtOH the performance varied with time; that is, the power density initially increased, and then declined exponentially.
Titulo: Direct utilization of methanol and ethanol in solid oxide fuel cells using Cu-Co(Ru)/Zr0.35Ce0.65O2-δ anodes

Sentencas: This behavior was likely a consequence of carbon deposition that initially improved electronic conductivity to the anode functional layer, and subsequently blocked active sites.
Titulo: Direct utilization of methanol and ethanol in solid oxide fuel cells using Cu-Co(Ru)/Zr0.35Ce0.65O2-δ anodes

Sentencas: For all cells, the performance was recovered by re-exposing the anode to humidified hydrogen.
Titulo: Direct utilization of methanol and ethanol in solid oxide fuel cells using Cu-Co(Ru)/Zr0.35Ce0.65O2-δ anodes

Sentencas: In some cases, the cell performance exceeded the initial activity measured in hydrogen.
Titulo: Direct utilization of methanol and ethanol in solid oxide fuel cells using Cu-Co(Ru)/Zr0.35Ce0.65O2-δ anodes

Sentencas: Thus, the direct utilization of MeOH and EtOH did not irreversibly deactivate the Co(Ru)/Zr0.35Ce0.65O2 anodes.
Titulo: Direct utilization of methanol and ethanol in solid oxide fuel cells using Cu-Co(Ru)/Zr0.35Ce0.65O2-δ anodes
